  "content": {
    "visible_text": "Rolling and Falling for Cyclists *During the COVID-19 pandemic, the San Francisco Dojo is closed for in-person community trainings. If you’d like to learn more about our current virtual offerings, please see our schedule for more info, or contact us * Do you ride a bike or motorcycle and want to learn how to fall safely? This workshop is for you! In this FREE workshop cyclists will have the opportunity to practice falling in a safe, padded environment . Rolling on the mat will train you to roll safely on the road as you learn to dive, survive, and return quickly to your feet. Using techniques borrowed from Judo (“the gentle way”), you’ll practice dispersing energy as you hit the ground, avoiding direct impact on your joints and bones. Diving rolls for distance throws, hard rolls for close-range impact, side falls and moving on the ground will all be covered. Partner movement drills will improve your reflexes, improving response time and honing the concept of living in the moment. Training awareness and focus help the smart city cyclist and weekend adventurer be prepared to make life-saving decisions instantly. When?  This free workshop is offered in Winter and Summer, on a Saturday 1:00 – 2:30 p.m. Where? Quantum Martial Arts, 2390 Mission Street, Suite #305, San Francisco . Who Teaches? Master Rachael Evans . What to Bring?  Water, comfortable clothes you can move in (no jeans, please). How to Register?  Please RSVP by emailing info@quantumsf.org , so we know to expect you. Workshops with no RSVP’s will be cancelled. What is the Cost?  This is a FREE community event. For more info: visit the Facebook event page or email info@quantumsf.org . Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
